<h2 id="Syntax">Syntax</h2>
<pre class="syntaxbox"><a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax" title="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax">Formal syntax</a>: <code><a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/color" title="">&lt;color&gt;</a></code>
</pre>
<h3 id="Values">Values</h3>
<dl><dt>
  <code>&lt;color&gt;</code></dt>
 <dd>
  Is a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/color_value" title=""><code>&lt;color&gt;</code></a> CSS value describing the color of the bottom border.</dd>
 <dt>
  <code>inherit</code></dt>
 <dd>
  Is a keyword denoting the color of the bottom border of the parent's element (which may be different from the <code>border-bottom-color</code> default value)</dd>
</dl>